analysis: The documents in this cluster primarily concern the modification, revocation, or establishment of land reservations and withdrawals for various purposes, including power sites, water reserves, national parks, military uses (ammunition depots and target ranges), and air navigation. They involve specific land descriptions, referencing various meridians and townships across multiple states. The documents reflect actions taken by Presidents Hoover and Roosevelt, often citing the authority of the Act of June 25, 1910, as amended.
title: Land Use and Resource Management Directives
